🧩 PART I — CADENCE PROFILES (Reusable Modes)

These are like “breathing presets”…
but delivered through text or audio.

Each one changes:
	•	rhythm
	•	spacing
	•	line structure

Which changes:
	•	breath
	•	state
	•	output

⸻

🟢 1. CALM / DOWNSHIFT

Goal: slow system, reduce anxiety, widen awareness

Cadence Rules:
	•	longer lines
	•	soft endings
	•	frequent spacing
	•	gentle repetition

⸻

Example:

You don’t need to rush this.

Let the line carry you…
just a little slower than usual…

so your breath has time to follow.

⸻

Nothing is chasing you here.

⸻

Just stay.

⸻

🔵 2. FOCUS / LOCK-IN

Goal: narrow attention, increase precision

Cadence Rules:
	•	short lines
	•	minimal spacing
	•	forward pressure
	•	direct language

⸻

Example:

Right here.

Stay with it.

Don’t drift.

Lock in.

⸻

Again.

Right here.

⸻

🟠 3. CONFIDENCE / PRESENCE

Goal: grounded, steady, controlled energy

Cadence Rules:
	•	medium lines
	•	deliberate pacing
	•	slight pauses
	•	declarative tone

⸻

Example:

You already know what to do.

You don’t need more input.

Just execute…
cleanly…
and without rushing.

⸻

🟣 4. RECOVERY / SLEEP

Goal: shut down system, prepare for rest

Cadence Rules:
	•	long flowing lines
	•	descending tone
	•	widening gaps
	•	soft repetition

⸻

Example:

Let your body settle…
a little deeper each breath…

nothing to hold…
nothing to maintain…

just drifting…
down.

⸻

🔴 5. INTENSITY / DRIVE

Goal: activation, momentum, action

Cadence Rules:
	•	tight stacks
	•	rapid hits
	•	minimal pause
	•	escalating rhythm

⸻

Example:

Move.

Now.

Don’t wait.

Go.

